{
  "page": "Assault on Harrenhal",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the battle during the War of the Five Kings, see <a href=\"/index.php/Yielding_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Yielding of Harrenhal\">Yielding of Harrenhal</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Assault on Harrenhal</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Conflict</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nOccupation of Harrenhal by the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/30px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/45px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/60px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a></b>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Aegon II Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/30px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/45px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/60px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">Greens</a></b>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Strong.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Strong.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/20px-House_Strong.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/30px-House_Strong.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/40px-House_Strong.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Strong\" title=\"House Strong\">House Strong</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Strong.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Strong.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/20px-House_Strong.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/30px-House_Strong.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/40px-House_Strong.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Strong\" title=\"Simon Strong\">Simon Strong</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Daemon on <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Strong garrison</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">None</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      None</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>assault on Harrenhal</b> was led by <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>, who conquered <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> for his wife, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>. It marked the opening of hostilities in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Conquest\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Conquest</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Assault_on_Harrenhal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The rival claims of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> led to <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">civil war</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. Rhaenyra's <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a> had more <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> than Aegon's <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a>, but most of their strength was focused around <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> instead of mainland <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. With <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a> effectively neutral because of disagreement between Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Grover_Tully\" title=\"Grover Tully\">Grover Tully</a> and his grandson, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Elmo_Tully\" title=\"Elmo Tully\">Elmo</a>, Rhaenyra's husband, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>, suggested <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> as a rallying point for potential supporters in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a>, Lord of Harrenhal, was a green supporter of Aegon, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Lucerys Velaryon</a> left Dragonstone to seek allies and <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> closed <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Bay\" title=\"Blackwater Bay\">Blackwater Bay</a>, Rhaenyra allowed her husband to command the assault on Harrenhal.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Conquest\">Conquest</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Assault_on_Harrenhal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Conquest\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Because Lord Larys Clubfoot served as Aegon II's <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_whisperers\" title=\"Master of whisperers\">master of whisperers</a> in King's Landing, his great-uncle<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> the elderly Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Strong\" title=\"Simon Strong\">Simon Strong</a> served as Larys's <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a> at Harrenhal. Prince Daemon flew on his dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a>, to the top of Harrenhal's <a href=\"/index.php/Kingspyre_Tower\" title=\"Kingspyre Tower\">Kingspyre Tower</a>, where <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren the Black</a> had died. Recalling the <a href=\"/index.php/Burning_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Burning of Harrenhal\">burning of Harrenhal</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion\" title=\"Balerion\">Balerion the Black Dread</a>, which had extinguished <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">House Hoare</a>, Simon decided to strike his banners and surrender the great ruined castle to Daemon. Simon and his grandsons were among a dozen hostages taken by Daemon, and the blacks requisitioned the wealth of House Strong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Assault_on_Harrenhal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The loss of Harrenhal shocked Aegon II and encouraged the blacks, who soon after won at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Burning_Mill\" title=\"Battle of the Burning Mill\">Burning Mill</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Stone_Hedge\" title=\"Taking of Stone Hedge\">Stone Hedge</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackwood\" title=\"House Blackwood\">House Blackwood</a> and other river lords gathered at Harrenhal, which was where Daemon approved of <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_and_Cheese\" title=\"Blood and Cheese\">Blood and Cheese</a> to avenge the death of Rhaenyra's son, Lucerys.\n</p><p>When Daemon learned that Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a> had left <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to retake Harrenhal, the blacks abandoned the castle and the rivermen marched to meet the <a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">westermen</a> of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Lannister\" title=\"Jason Lannister\">Jason Lannister</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_the_Red_Fork\" title=\"Battle at the Red Fork\">Red Fork</a>. While Criston and Aemond retook Harrenhal without bloodshed, their absence contributed to the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Fall of King&#39;s Landing\">fall of King's Landing</a> to Daemon and Rhaenyra. Aemond ordered the executions of <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Strong\" title=\"Simon Strong\">Simon Strong</a> and his kin, although he spared <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Rivers\" title=\"Alys Rivers\">Alys Rivers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Assault_on_Harrenhal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We have friends in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, though not all of them dare show their colors yet. We need a place where they can gather, a toehold on the mainland large enough to house a sizeable host, and strong enough to hold against whatever forces <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">the usurper</a> can send against us. Here. <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_council\" title=\"Black council\">black council</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Assault_on_Harrenhal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Blacks and the Greens.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyr